# Documentation

Every feature requires documentation updates proportional to its impact.

## Knowledge base layout

```text
docs/                    # Living engineering knowledge base
  architecture/
  business/
  api/
  database/
  features/
  adr/                   # Architecture Decision Records
  development/
  testing/
  security/
Docs/                    # Product docs — in chatbotmaker-docs repo (private)
```

Update the relevant section when behavior, APIs, schema, or architecture changes.

## Required (when applicable)

- **API docs** — contracts in `docs/api/` before implementation (`api-contract-first` skill)
- **Architecture notes** — `docs/architecture/` or ADR in `docs/adr/`
- **README updates** — setup, env vars, run commands
- **Migration notes** — `docs/database/`
- **ADR** — significant decisions (problem, options, choice, trade-offs)

## ADR format (`docs/adr/NNNN-title.md`)

1. Status (proposed | accepted | superseded)
2. Context / problem
3. Options considered
4. Decision
5. Consequences and trade-offs

## Rules

Document during implementation. If a future engineer cannot operate or extend the feature from docs + code, documentation is incomplete.
